**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Description:** The image shows a close-up view of a silver car's side panel near the wheel well.

**Location of Damage:** There appears to be a visible scratch or dent on the side panel of the car, located just above the wheel well area. The damage seems to be a linear scratch running horizontally along the panel.

**Type of Damage:** The damage appears to be a superficial scratch rather than a deeper dent. It does not seem to affect the structural integrity of the panel but may require cosmetic repair to restore the vehicle's appearance.

**Conclusion:** The vehicle has sustained a minor scratch on its side panel near the wheel well. No other significant damage is observed in this image.

**Recommendation:** The scratch should be assessed further by a professional to determine if it requires touch-up paint or any additional repairs.
